This is the second time a jury has been unable to determine whether Ray Tensing was guilty of murder or voluntary manslaughter over the July 2015 death of Sam Dubose.

Cara Owsley / AP Tensing and his defense attorney, Stewart Mathews, on June 8.

An Ohio judge declared a second mistrial Friday in the case of Ray Tensing, a University of Cincinnati police officer who shot and killed an unarmed black man during a traffic stop, after a jury deadlocked and could not reach a verdict.
